text:
(1)
Feast of Our Lady of Mt. Carmel: Parade, marching north on First Avenue, between 109th and 110th Streets, showing the spectators in the houses and shops on the west side of the Avenue. Notice the three penitent women marching barefoot.
July 16, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
Parade, marching east on 11th Street, at and adjoining S.E. corner of Second Avenue. Notice the picture-banner of St.
Nicholas of Savoy.
July 16, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
Parade, women and children bearing small towers of candles.
The street is unidentified.
July 16, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

August 31, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
